<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-329-869  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 329 869.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Feb 1989 v26 n2 p17(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Creative networking at Baltimore investment house links clientswith trading floor. (Alex, Brown andamp; Sons)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kubitz, Barb.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Alex, Brown and Sons, a company that manages about $1 trillion inassets, makes extensive use of videoconferencing.andP;  The firmoperates interactive digital video conference rooms where videoimages and information are displayed on two large screens.andP;  Thedisplays are broadcast to three different video sites as well as20 other offices across the US.andP;  The videoconference systememploys the VSI Spectra system and a Compression Labs digitalvideo codecs and operates on Sprint's Meeting Channel service atbetween 384K-bps and 768K-bps.andP;  The system provides good imagingand sound without the expense of a satellite channel.andP;  The factthat the network is digital also allows the information to beencrypted to Defense Encryption Standards and provides an extrameasure of security for sensitive information.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Alex Brown and Sons Inc. (communication systems).andO;Topic:     Brokerage IndustryVideoconferencingApplicationsDigital CommunicationsNetworks.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>